    background: `Heidi Lloce Mendoza is an accountant and former public servant. She earned her Accountancy degree in 1983 and passed the CPA exam in 1984. She later pursued post-graduate studies, completing a Master of Public Administration in 1996 and a Master in National Security Administration in 2003. Mendoza began her career at COA as an Auditing Aide II and rose to the position of Chief of the Value for Money Audit Division. In 2011, she was appointed COA commissioner by President Aquino and served until 2015, when she became officer-in-charge. She played a key role in exposing government corruption, including scandals involving overpriced medical supplies and money laundering. In 2015, she was appointed Undersecretary-General for the UN Office of Internal Oversight Services, serving until 2019. She has also worked as an external auditor for several UN organizations. Mendoza is married to Meynardo Mendoza, a history professor, and they have three children.`,
